      "span_text": "Echocardiographic screening is part of the evaluation of every patient presenting with hypotension, breathlessness, chest discomfort, and/or symptoms of low cardiac output after catheter ablation of AF.  TTE screening for pericardial effusion after even uncomplicated catheter ablation of AF is performed in some labs."
